## Content Management

### Using Frontmatter Data
```tsx
export const PropertyTags = component$(() => {
  const { frontmatter } = useDocumentHead();
  
  if (!frontmatter.tags || frontmatter.tags.length === 0) {
    return null;
  }
  
  return (
    <div class="property-tags">
      <h4>Tags</h4>
      <ul class="tag-list">
        {frontmatter.tags.map((tag: string) => (
          <li key={`tag-${tag}`} class="tag">
            <a href={`/tags/${tag}`}>{tag}</a>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
});
```

## Best Practices
- ✅ **Consistent Structure**: Use the same frontmatter pattern across all MDX files
- ✅ **Component Reuse**: Create reusable components for common patterns
- ✅ **SEO Optimization**: Always include proper meta tags and Open Graph data
- ✅ **Accessibility**: Use semantic HTML and proper heading hierarchy
- ✅ **Performance**: Optimize images and lazy load heavy components
- ✅ **Real Estate Specific**: Include comprehensive property information in frontmatter
- ✅ **Location Data**: Always include zip codes and neighborhood information
- ✅ **Interactive Elements**: Embed property search, maps, and contact forms